<TITLE> Nazmul Huda jailed for 7 years, Sigma for 3 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 27 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Monday jailed Nazmul Huda for seven years and his wife Sigma Huda for three years in a Tk 2.4 crore bribery case. Judge Amar Kumar Roy of the Special Judge's Court-2 of Dhaka convicted the former communications minister of taking Tk 2.4 crore in three bank cheques in bribe from Mir Zahir Hossain, managing director of construction firm Mir Akhtar Hossain Ltd and elder brother of FBCCI president Mir Nasir Hossain. Huda had taken the bribe in exchange for awarding Hossain five contracts under the Roads and Highways Department tun by his ministry. The former BNP minister has been fined Tk 2.5 crore or he has to serve one more year out in jail. The court also ordered authorities to confiscate Tk 2.4 crore he had taken in bribe. Sigma has been convicted of abetting her husband in committing the crime by depositing the cheques in her bank accounts in the name of her Bangla-language weekly magazine Khoborer Antoraley. She withdrew Tk 1 crore from the account and opened an FDR in the name of their two daughters. The Anticorruption Commission's deputy director Md Shafiqul Islam filed the case against Huda and his wife with Dhanmondi Police Station on March 21. The special court housed in the parliament complex framed charges on July 5. A total of 48 people gave their deposition from July 9 through to July 23, 40 for the state and eight for the defendants. The hearing started on August 7 and on August 14, judge Roy set the verdict date after closing hearing. bdnews24.com/pc/shb
